tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE student_interactions (
  student_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  lesson_id UUID,
  interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
  interaction_duration INT
)

CREATE TABLE StudentInteractions (
    student_id INT,
    lesson_id INT,
    interaction_date DATE,
    interaction_duration INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE Lessons (
    lesson_id INT,
    lesson_name VARCHAR(100),
    lesson_subject VARCHAR(50),
    lesson_difficulty VARCHAR(20),
    lesson_duration INT
);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceAnalysis (
    analysis_id INT,
    student_id INT,
    lesson_id INT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    analysis_score INT,
    analysis_feedback TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE lessons (
    lesson_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lesson_name VARCHAR(100),
    lesson_description TEXT,
    lesson_type VARCHAR(50),
    is_completed BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    lesson_id INT,
    interaction_date DATE,
    interaction_duration INT,
    interaction_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    lesson_id INT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    completion_status BOOLEAN,
    performance_score INT
);

CREATE TABLE students (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_name STRING,
    lesson_completed_date DATE,
    lesson_score FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE lessons (
    lesson_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lesson_name STRING,
    lesson_description STRING,
    lesson_difficulty INT
)

CREATE TABLE lesson_interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    lesson_id INT,
    interaction_date DATE,
    interaction_type STRING
)

CREATE TABLE student_performance (
    performance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    lesson_id INT,
    performance_score FLOAT,
    performance_feedback STRING
)

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lesson_id INT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    analysis_result STRING
)
